comments: Towns (MIN) is moving alongside Gallinari's (OKC) path, but turns into him and initiates contact that affects Gallinari's SQBR.
Covington (MIN) cleanly dislodges the ball from Adams (OKC) during rebounding.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes contact to Bell's (MIN) arm as he is starting his upward shooting motion.
Gallinari (OKC) is already in Okogie's (MIN) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with the backboard but the contact does not affect the ability for Paul's (OKC) shot to be scored.
Adams (OKC) and Towns (MIN) make incidental contact with one another off ball.
Towns (MIN) is already in Paul's (OKC) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Paul (OKC) legally contests Towns' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with the ball after Schroder's (OKC) shot attempt makes contact with the backboard.
Adams (OKC) legally contests Towns' (MIN) driving shot attempt.
Okogie (MIN) makes marginal contact with Schroder (OKC) during his drive.
Adams (OKC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Towns (MIN) during rebounding.
Towns (MIN) is already in Schroder's (OKC) path and he absorbs the contact to his upper body.  Any ensuing foot to foot contact is considered incidental.
Dort (OKC) and Napier (MIN) make incidental contact with one another as they attempt to secure the loose ball.
Paul (OKC) releases from contact with Towns (MIN) as part of his legal step-back move.
Paul (OKC) initiates marginal contact with Okogie (MIN) when he extends his leg as part of his jump shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) makes incidental contact with Paul's (OKC) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Adams (OKC) makes incidental contact with Bell (MIN) during rebounding.
Adams (OKC) commits a take foul on Bell (MIN).
Paul (OKC) and Okogie (MIN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Okogie (MIN) grabs the rebound and has possession of the ball.  The Timberwolves signal for a timeout prior to Paul (OKC) making clean contact with the ball.
Bell (MIN) enters the game with his jersey untucked and a delay of game is correctly called.  This is the Timberwolves' second delay of game violation and they are assessed a delay technical.
Paul (OKC) commits a take foul on Towns (MIN).
Schroder (OKC) does not push off Teague (MIN) and affect his ability to defend the pass.
